15/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- A delegation representing the European Commission praised the progress Albania has made and urged it to proceed with reforms.
The EU-Albania Consultative Task Force met in Tirana on 13 and 14 November, focusing on implementation of Brussels' recommendations and Tirana's hopes of starting negotiations for an association accord next month.
Albania also received high marks Thursday from CoE Secretary General Walter Schwimmer.
He met with Minister of Labour and Social Affairs Valentina Leskaj in Strasbourg, and congratulated her on Albania's ratification of the revised European Social Charter, calling it an important step towards European integration.
(ATA, CoE web site - 14/11/02)
